<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="AppDiffEVT" checkit-title="Extreme Value Theorem">
    <statement>
        <p> 
Explain how to find the absolute minimum and absolute maximum values of the
function <m>f(x)=-2 \, x^{3} + 6 \, x^{2} + 90 \, x - 28</m> on the interval <m>[-7,1]</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
The absolute extrema may occur at these <m>x</m>-values:
<m>-7, -3, 1</m>.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><p><m>f(-7)=322</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(-3)=-190</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(1)=66</m></p></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
Thus the absolute minimum is <m>-190</m> and the absolute
maximum is <m>322</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
(The value <m>f(5)=322</m>
is ignored as <m>5</m> isn't in the given interval.)
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
